2722void CXXNameMangler::mangleExtFunctionInfo(const FunctionType *T) {
2723 // Fast path.
2724 if (T->getExtInfo() == FunctionType::ExtInfo())
2725 return;
2726
2727 // Vendor-specific qualifiers are emitted in reverse alphabetical order.
2728 // This will get more complicated in the future if we mangle other
2729 // things here; but for now, since we mangle ns_returns_retained as
2730 // a qualifier on the result type, we can get away with this:
2731 StringRef CCQualifier = getCallingConvQualifierName(T->getExtInfo().getCC());
2732 if (!CCQualifier.empty())
2733 mangleVendorQualifier(CCQualifier);
2734
2735 // FIXME: regparm
2736 // FIXME: noreturn
2737}
2738
2739void
2740CXXNameMangler::mangleExtParameterInfo(FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo PI) {
2741 // Vendor-specific qualifiers are emitted in reverse alphabetical order.
2742
2743 // Note that these are *not* substitution candidates. Demanglers might
2744 // have trouble with this if the parameter type is fully substituted.
2745
2746 switch (PI.getABI()) {
2747 case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
2748 break;
2749
2750 // All of these start with "swift", so they come before "ns_consumed".
2751 case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
2752 case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
2753 case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult:
2754 mangleVendorQualifier(getParameterABISpelling(PI.getABI()));
2755 break;
2756 }
2757
2758 if (PI.isConsumed())
2759 mangleVendorQualifier("ns_consumed");
2760
2761 if (PI.isNoEscape())
2762 mangleVendorQualifier("noescape");
2763}

2765// <type> ::= <function-type>
2766// <function-type> ::= [<CV-qualifiers>] F [Y]
2767// <bare-function-type> [<ref-qualifier>] E
2768void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const FunctionProtoType *T) {
2769 mangleExtFunctionInfo(T);
2770
2771 // Mangle CV-qualifiers, if present. These are 'this' qualifiers,
2772 // e.g. "const" in "int (A::*)() const".
2773 mangleQualifiers(T->getMethodQuals());
2774
2775 // Mangle instantiation-dependent exception-specification, if present,
2776 // per cxx-abi-dev proposal on 2016-10-11.
2777 if (T->hasInstantiationDependentExceptionSpec()) {
2778 if (isComputedNoexcept(T->getExceptionSpecType())) {
2779 Out << "DO";
2780 mangleExpression(T->getNoexceptExpr());
2781 Out << "E";
2782 } else {
2783 assert(T->getExceptionSpecType() == EST_Dynamic);
2784 Out << "Dw";
2785 for (auto ExceptTy : T->exceptions())
2786 mangleType(ExceptTy);
2787 Out << "E";
2788 }
2789 } else if (T->isNothrow()) {
2790 Out << "Do";
2791 }
2792
2793 Out << 'F';
2794
2795 // FIXME: We don't have enough information in the AST to produce the 'Y'
2796 // encoding for extern "C" function types.
2797 mangleBareFunctionType(T, /*MangleReturnType=*/true);
2798
2799 // Mangle the ref-qualifier, if present.
2800 mangleRefQualifier(T->getRefQualifier());
2801
2802 Out << 'E';
2803}
2804
2805void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const FunctionNoProtoType *T) {
2806 // Function types without prototypes can arise when mangling a function type
2807 // within an overloadable function in C. We mangle these as the absence of any
2808 // parameter types (not even an empty parameter list).
2809 Out << 'F';
2810
2811 FunctionTypeDepthState saved = FunctionTypeDepth.push();
2812
2813 FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
2814 mangleType(T->getReturnType());
2815 FunctionTypeDepth.leaveResultType();
2816
2817 FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
2818 Out << 'E';
2819}
2820
2821void CXXNameMangler::mangleBareFunctionType(const FunctionProtoType *Proto,
2822 bool MangleReturnType,
2823 const FunctionDecl *FD) {
2824 // Record that we're in a function type. See mangleFunctionParam
2825 // for details on what we're trying to achieve here.
2826 FunctionTypeDepthState saved = FunctionTypeDepth.push();
2827
2828 // <bare-function-type> ::= <signature type>+
2829 if (MangleReturnType) {
2830 FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
2831
2832 // Mangle ns_returns_retained as an order-sensitive qualifier here.
2833 if (Proto->getExtInfo().getProducesResult() && FD == nullptr)
2834 mangleVendorQualifier("ns_returns_retained");
2835
2836 // Mangle the return type without any direct ARC ownership qualifiers.
2837 QualType ReturnTy = Proto->getReturnType();
2838 if (ReturnTy.getObjCLifetime()) {
2839 auto SplitReturnTy = ReturnTy.split();
2840 SplitReturnTy.Quals.removeObjCLifetime();
2841 ReturnTy = getASTContext().getQualifiedType(SplitReturnTy);
2842 }
2843 mangleType(ReturnTy);
2844
2845 FunctionTypeDepth.leaveResultType();
2846 }
2847
2848 if (Proto->getNumParams() == 0 && !Proto->isVariadic()) {
2849 // <builtin-type> ::= v # void
2850 Out << 'v';
2851
2852 FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
2853 return;
2854 }
2855
2856 assert(!FD || FD->getNumParams() == Proto->getNumParams());
2857 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Proto->getNumParams(); I != E; ++I) {
2858 // Mangle extended parameter info as order-sensitive qualifiers here.
2859 if (Proto->hasExtParameterInfos() && FD == nullptr) {
2860 mangleExtParameterInfo(Proto->getExtParameterInfo(I));
2861 }
2862
2863 // Mangle the type.
2864 QualType ParamTy = Proto->getParamType(I);
2865 mangleType(Context.getASTContext().getSignatureParameterType(ParamTy));
2866
2867 if (FD) {
2868 if (auto *Attr = FD->getParamDecl(I)->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>()) {
2869 // Attr can only take 1 character, so we can hardcode the length below.
2870 assert(Attr->getType() <= 9 && Attr->getType() >= 0);
2871 if (Attr->isDynamic())
2872 Out << "U25pass_dynamic_object_size" << Attr->getType();
2873 else
2874 Out << "U17pass_object_size" << Attr->getType();
2875 }
2876 }
2877 }
2878
2879 FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
2880
2881 // <builtin-type> ::= z # ellipsis
2882 if (Proto->isVariadic())
2883 Out << 'z';
2884}

2930// <type> ::= <pointer-to-member-type>
2931// <pointer-to-member-type> ::= M <class type> <member type>
2932void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const MemberPointerType *T) {
2933 Out << 'M';
2934 mangleType(QualType(T->getClass(), 0));
2935 QualType PointeeType = T->getPointeeType();
2936 if (const FunctionProtoType *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(PointeeType)) {
2937 mangleType(FPT);
2938
2939 // Itanium C++ ABI 5.1.8:
2940 //
2941 // The type of a non-static member function is considered to be different,
2942 // for the purposes of substitution, from the type of a namespace-scope or
2943 // static member function whose type appears similar. The types of two
2944 // non-static member functions are considered to be different, for the
2945 // purposes of substitution, if the functions are members of different
2946 // classes. In other words, for the purposes of substitution, the class of
2947 // which the function is a member is considered part of the type of
2948 // function.
2949
2950 // Given that we already substitute member function pointers as a
2951 // whole, the net effect of this rule is just to unconditionally
2952 // suppress substitution on the function type in a member pointer.
2953 // We increment the SeqID here to emulate adding an entry to the
2954 // substitution table.
2955 ++SeqID;
2956 } else
2957 mangleType(PointeeType);
2958}

3008// ARM's ABI for Neon vector types specifies that they should be mangled as
3009// if they are structs (to match ARM's initial implementation). The
3010// vector type must be one of the special types predefined by ARM.
3011void CXXNameMangler::mangleNeonVectorType(const VectorType *T) {
3012 QualType EltType = T->getElementType();
3013 assert(EltType->isBuiltinType() && "Neon vector element not a BuiltinType");
3014 const char *EltName = nullptr;
3015 if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorType::NeonPolyVector) {
3016 switch (cast<BuiltinType>(EltType)->getKind()) {
3017 case BuiltinType::SChar:
3018 case BuiltinType::UChar:
3019 EltName = "poly8_t";
3020 break;
3021 case BuiltinType::Short:
3022 case BuiltinType::UShort:
3023 EltName = "poly16_t";
3024 break;
3025 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
3026 EltName = "poly64_t";
3027 break;
3028 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected Neon polynomial vector element type");
3029 }
3030 } else {
3031 switch (cast<BuiltinType>(EltType)->getKind()) {
3032 case BuiltinType::SChar: EltName = "int8_t"; break;
3033 case BuiltinType::UChar: EltName = "uint8_t"; break;
3034 case BuiltinType::Short: EltName = "int16_t"; break;
3035 case BuiltinType::UShort: EltName = "uint16_t"; break;
3036 case BuiltinType::Int: EltName = "int32_t"; break;
3037 case BuiltinType::UInt: EltName = "uint32_t"; break;
3038 case BuiltinType::LongLong: EltName = "int64_t"; break;
3039 case BuiltinType::ULongLong: EltName = "uint64_t"; break;
3040 case BuiltinType::Double: EltName = "float64_t"; break;
3041 case BuiltinType::Float: EltName = "float32_t"; break;
3042 case BuiltinType::Half: EltName = "float16_t";break;
3043 default:
3044 llvm_unreachable("unexpected Neon vector element type");
3045 }
3046 }
3047 const char *BaseName = nullptr;
3048 unsigned BitSize = (T->getNumElements() *
3049 getASTContext().getTypeSize(EltType));
3050 if (BitSize == 64)
3051 BaseName = "__simd64_";
3052 else {
3053 assert(BitSize == 128 && "Neon vector type not 64 or 128 bits");
3054 BaseName = "__simd128_";
3055 }
3056 Out << strlen(BaseName) + strlen(EltName);
3057 Out << BaseName << EltName;
3058}

3143// GNU extension: vector types
3144// <type> ::= <vector-type>
3145// <vector-type> ::= Dv <positive dimension number> _
3146// <extended element type>
3147// ::= Dv [<dimension expression>] _ <element type>
3148// <extended element type> ::= <element type>
3149// ::= p # AltiVec vector pixel
3150// ::= b # Altivec vector bool
3151void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const VectorType *T) {
3152 if ((T->getVectorKind() == VectorType::NeonVector ||
3153 T->getVectorKind() == VectorType::NeonPolyVector)) {
3154 llvm::Triple Target = getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple();
3155 llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch =
3156 getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch();
3157 if ((Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64 ||
3158 Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64_be) && !Target.isOSDarwin())
3159 mangleAArch64NeonVectorType(T);
3160 else
3161 mangleNeonVectorType(T);
3162 return;
3163 }
3164 Out << "Dv" << T->getNumElements() << '_';
3165 if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorType::AltiVecPixel)
3166 Out << 'p';
3167 else if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorType::AltiVecBool)
3168 Out << 'b';
3169 else
3170 mangleType(T->getElementType());
3171}

3224void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const ObjCObjectType *T) {

3228
3229 if (!T->qual_empty()) {
3230 // Mangle protocol qualifiers.
3231 SmallString<64> QualStr;
3232 llvm::raw_svector_ostream QualOS(QualStr);
3233 QualOS << "objcproto";
3234 for (const auto *I : T->quals()) {
3235 StringRef name = I->getName();
3236 QualOS << name.size() << name;
3237 }
3238 Out << 'U' << QualStr.size() << QualStr;
3239 }
3240
3241 mangleType(T->getBaseType());
3242
3243 if (T->isSpecialized()) {
3244 // Mangle type arguments as I <type>+ E
3245 Out << 'I';
3246 for (auto typeArg : T->getTypeArgs())
3247 mangleType(typeArg);
3248 Out << 'E';
3249 }
3250}

3253 Out << "U13block_pointer";
3254 mangleType(T->getPointeeType());
3255}

3257void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const InjectedClassNameType *T) {
3258 // Mangle injected class name types as if the user had written the
3259 // specialization out fully. It may not actually be possible to see
3260 // this mangling, though.
3261 mangleType(T->getInjectedSpecializationType());
3262}

3264void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const TemplateSpecializationType *T) {
3265 if (TemplateDecl *TD = T->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl()) {
3266 mangleTemplateName(TD, T->getArgs(), T->getNumArgs());
3267 } else {
3268 if (mangleSubstitution(QualType(T, 0)))
3269 return;
3270
3271 mangleTemplatePrefix(T->getTemplateName());
3272
3273 // FIXME: GCC does not appear to mangle the template arguments when
3274 // the template in question is a dependent template name. Should we
3275 // emulate that badness?
3276 mangleTemplateArgs(T->getArgs(), T->getNumArgs());
3277 addSubstitution(QualType(T, 0));
3278 }
3279}
3280
3281void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DependentNameType *T) {
3282 // Proposal by cxx-abi-dev, 2014-03-26
3283 // <class-enum-type> ::= <name> # non-dependent or dependent type name or
3284 // # dependent elaborated type specifier using
3285 // # 'typename'
3286 // ::= Ts <name> # dependent elaborated type specifier using
3287 // # 'struct' or 'class'
3288 // ::= Tu <name> # dependent elaborated type specifier using
3289 // # 'union'
3290 // ::= Te <name> # dependent elaborated type specifier using
3291 // # 'enum'
3292 switch (T->getKeyword()) {
3293 case ETK_None:
3294 case ETK_Typename:
3295 break;
3296 case ETK_Struct:
3297 case ETK_Class:
3298 case ETK_Interface:
3299 Out << "Ts";
3300 break;
3301 case ETK_Union:
3302 Out << "Tu";
3303 break;
3304 case ETK_Enum:
3305 Out << "Te";
3306 break;
3307 }
3308 // Typename types are always nested
3309 Out << 'N';
3310 manglePrefix(T->getQualifier());
3311 mangleSourceName(T->getIdentifier());
3312 Out << 'E';
3313}
3314
3315void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DependentTemplateSpecializationType *T) {
3316 // Dependently-scoped template types are nested if they have a prefix.
3317 Out << 'N';
3318
3319 // TODO: avoid making this TemplateName.
3320 TemplateName Prefix =
3321 getASTContext().getDependentTemplateName(T->getQualifier(),
3322 T->getIdentifier());
3323 mangleTemplatePrefix(Prefix);
3324
3325 // FIXME: GCC does not appear to mangle the template arguments when
3326 // the template in question is a dependent template name. Should we
3327 // emulate that badness?
3328 mangleTemplateArgs(T->getArgs(), T->getNumArgs());
3329 Out << 'E';
3330}

3333 // FIXME: this is pretty unsatisfactory, but there isn't an obvious
3334 // "extension with parameters" mangling.
3335 Out << "u6typeof";
3336}

3338void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const TypeOfExprType *T) {

3343
3344void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DecltypeType *T) {
3345 Expr *E = T->getUnderlyingExpr();
3346
3347 // type ::= Dt <expression> E # decltype of an id-expression
3348 // # or class member access
3349 // ::= DT <expression> E # decltype of an expression
3350
3351 // This purports to be an exhaustive list of id-expressions and
3352 // class member accesses. Note that we do not ignore parentheses;
3353 // parentheses change the semantics of decltype for these
3354 // expressions (and cause the mangler to use the other form).
3355 if (isa<DeclRefExpr>(E) ||
3356 isa<MemberExpr>(E) ||
3357 isa<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E) ||
3358 isa<DependentScopeDeclRefExpr>(E) ||
3359 isa<CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr>(E) ||
3360 isa<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(E))
3361 Out << "Dt";
3362 else
3363 Out << "DT";
3364 mangleExpression(E);
3365 Out << 'E';
3366}
3367
3368void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const UnaryTransformType *T) {
3369 // If this is dependent, we need to record that. If not, we simply
3370 // mangle it as the underlying type since they are equivalent.
3371 if (T->isDependentType()) {
3372 Out << 'U';
3373
3374 switch (T->getUTTKind()) {
3375 case UnaryTransformType::EnumUnderlyingType:
3376 Out << "3eut";
3377 break;
3378 }
3379 }
3380
3381 mangleType(T->getBaseType());
3382}
3383
3384void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const AutoType *T) {
3385 assert(T->getDeducedType().isNull() &&
3386 "Deduced AutoType shouldn't be handled here!");
3387 assert(T->getKeyword() != AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType &&
3388 "shouldn't need to mangle __auto_type!");
3389 // <builtin-type> ::= Da # auto
3390 // ::= Dc # decltype(auto)
3391 Out << (T->isDecltypeAuto() ? "Dc" : "Da");
3392}

3396 // here in some cases.

3398 if (D.isNull())
3399 mangleUnscopedTemplateName(T->getTemplateName(), nullptr);
3400 else

3418void CXXNameMangler::mangleIntegerLiteral(QualType T,
3419 const llvm::APSInt &Value) {
3420 // <expr-primary> ::= L <type> <value number> E # integer literal
3421 Out << 'L';
3422
3423 mangleType(T);
3424 if (T->isBooleanType()) {
3425 // Boolean values are encoded as 0/1.
3426 Out << (Value.getBoolValue() ? '1' : '0');
3427 } else {
3428 mangleNumber(Value);
3429 }
3430 Out << 'E';
3431
3432}
3433
3434void CXXNameMangler::mangleMemberExprBase(const Expr *Base, bool IsArrow) {
3435 // Ignore member expressions involving anonymous unions.
3436 while (const auto *RT = Base->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
3437 if (!RT->getDecl()->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
3438 break;
3439 const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Base);
3440 if (!ME)
3441 break;
3442 Base = ME->getBase();
3443 IsArrow = ME->isArrow();
3444 }
3445
3446 if (Base->isImplicitCXXThis()) {
3447 // Note: GCC mangles member expressions to the implicit 'this' as
3448 // *this., whereas we represent them as this->. The Itanium C++ ABI
3449 // does not specify anything here, so we follow GCC.
3450 Out << "dtdefpT";
3451 } else {
3452 Out << (IsArrow ? "pt" : "dt");
3453 mangleExpression(Base);
3454 }
3455}
3456
3457/// Mangles a member expression.
3458void CXXNameMangler::mangleMemberExpr(const Expr *base,
3459 bool isArrow,
3460 NestedNameSpecifier *qualifier,
3461 NamedDecl *firstQualifierLookup,
3462 DeclarationName member,
3463 const TemplateArgumentLoc *TemplateArgs,
3464 unsigned NumTemplateArgs,
3465 unsigned arity) {
3466 // <expression> ::= dt <expression> <unresolved-name>
3467 // ::= pt <expression> <unresolved-name>
3468 if (base)
3469 mangleMemberExprBase(base, isArrow);
3470 mangleUnresolvedName(qualifier, member, TemplateArgs, NumTemplateArgs, arity);
3471}
3472
3473/// Look at the callee of the given call expression and determine if
3474/// it's a parenthesized id-expression which would have triggered ADL
3475/// otherwise.
3476static bool isParenthesizedADLCallee(const CallExpr *call) {
3477 const Expr *callee = call->getCallee();
3478 const Expr *fn = callee->IgnoreParens();
3479
3480 // Must be parenthesized. IgnoreParens() skips __extension__ nodes,
3481 // too, but for those to appear in the callee, it would have to be
3482 // parenthesized.
3483 if (callee == fn) return false;
3484
3485 // Must be an unresolved lookup.
3486 const UnresolvedLookupExpr *lookup = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(fn);
3487 if (!lookup) return false;
3488
3489 assert(!lookup->requiresADL());
3490
3491 // Must be an unqualified lookup.
3492 if (lookup->getQualifier()) return false;
3493
3494 // Must not have found a class member. Note that if one is a class
3495 // member, they're all class members.
3496 if (lookup->getNumDecls() > 0 &&
3497 (*lookup->decls_begin())->isCXXClassMember())
3498 return false;
3499
3500 // Otherwise, ADL would have been triggered.
3501 return true;
3502}
3503
3504void CXXNameMangler::mangleCastExpression(const Expr *E, StringRef CastEncoding) {
3505 const ExplicitCastExpr *ECE = cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(E);
3506 Out << CastEncoding;
3507 mangleType(ECE->getType());
3508 mangleExpression(ECE->getSubExpr());
3509}

3511void CXXNameMangler::mangleInitListElements(const InitListExpr *InitList) {
3512 if (auto *Syntactic = InitList->getSyntacticForm())
3513 InitList = Syntactic;
3514 for (unsigned i = 0, e = InitList->getNumInits(); i != e; ++i)
3515 mangleExpression(InitList->getInit(i));
3516}
3517
3518void CXXNameMangler::mangleDeclRefExpr(const NamedDecl *D) {
3519 switch (D->getKind()) {
3520 default:
3521 // <expr-primary> ::= L <mangled-name> E # external name
3522 Out << 'L';
3523 mangle(D);
3524 Out << 'E';
3525 break;
3526
3527 case Decl::ParmVar:
3528 mangleFunctionParam(cast<ParmVarDecl>(D));
3529 break;
3530
3531 case Decl::EnumConstant: {
3532 const EnumConstantDecl *ED = cast<EnumConstantDecl>(D);
3533 mangleIntegerLiteral(ED->getType(), ED->getInitVal());
3534 break;
3535 }
3536
3537 case Decl::NonTypeTemplateParm:
3538 const NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *PD = cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(D);
3539 mangleTemplateParameter(PD->getIndex());
3540 break;
3541 }
3542}
3543
3544void CXXNameMangler::mangleExpression(const Expr *E, unsigned Arity) {
3545 // <expression> ::= <unary operator-name> <expression>
3546 // ::= <binary operator-name> <expression> <expression>
3547 // ::= <trinary operator-name> <expression> <expression> <expression>
3548 // ::= cv <type> expression # conversion with one argument
3549 // ::= cv <type> _ <expression>* E # conversion with a different number of arguments
3550 // ::= dc <type> <expression> # dynamic_cast<type> (expression)
3551 // ::= sc <type> <expression> # static_cast<type> (expression)
3552 // ::= cc <type> <expression> # const_cast<type> (expression)
3553 // ::= rc <type> <expression> # reinterpret_cast<type> (expression)
3554 // ::= st <type> # sizeof (a type)
3555 // ::= at <type> # alignof (a type)
3556 // ::= <template-param>
3557 // ::= <function-param>
3558 // ::= sr <type> <unqualified-name> # dependent name
3559 // ::= sr <type> <unqualified-name> <template-args> # dependent template-id
3560 // ::= ds <expression> <expression> # expr.*expr
3561 // ::= sZ <template-param> # size of a parameter pack
3562 // ::= sZ <function-param> # size of a function parameter pack
3563 // ::= <expr-primary>
3564 // <expr-primary> ::= L <type> <value number> E # integer literal
3565 // ::= L <type <value float> E # floating literal
3566 // ::= L <mangled-name> E # external name
3567 // ::= fpT # 'this' expression
3568 QualType ImplicitlyConvertedToType;
3569
3570recurse:
3571 switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
3572 case Expr::NoStmtClass:
3573#define ABSTRACT_STMT(Type)
3574#define EXPR(Type, Base)
3575#define STMT(Type, Base) \
3576 case Expr::Type##Class:
3577#include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
3578 // fallthrough
3579
3580 // These all can only appear in local or variable-initialization
3581 // contexts and so should never appear in a mangling.
3582 case Expr::AddrLabelExprClass:
3583 case Expr::DesignatedInitUpdateExprClass:
3584 case Expr::ImplicitValueInitExprClass:
3585 case Expr::ArrayInitLoopExprClass:
3586 case Expr::ArrayInitIndexExprClass:
3587 case Expr::NoInitExprClass:
3588 case Expr::ParenListExprClass:
3589 case Expr::LambdaExprClass:
3590 case Expr::MSPropertyRefExprClass:
3591 case Expr::MSPropertySubscriptExprClass:
3592 case Expr::TypoExprClass: // This should no longer exist in the AST by now.
3593 case Expr::OMPArraySectionExprClass:
3594 case Expr::CXXInheritedCtorInitExprClass:
3595 llvm_unreachable("unexpected statement kind");
3596
3597 case Expr::ConstantExprClass:
3598 E = cast<ConstantExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
3599 goto recurse;
3600
3601 // FIXME: invent manglings for all these.
3602 case Expr::BlockExprClass:
3603 case Expr::ChooseExprClass:
3604 case Expr::CompoundLiteralExprClass:
3605 case Expr::ExtVectorElementExprClass:
3606 case Expr::GenericSelectionExprClass:
3607 case Expr::ObjCEncodeExprClass:
3608 case Expr::ObjCIsaExprClass:
3609 case Expr::ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
3610 case Expr::ObjCMessageExprClass:
3611 case Expr::ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
3612 case Expr::ObjCProtocolExprClass:
3613 case Expr::ObjCSelectorExprClass:
3614 case Expr::ObjCStringLiteralClass:
3615 case Expr::ObjCBoxedExprClass:
3616 case Expr::ObjCArrayLiteralClass:
3617 case Expr::ObjCDictionaryLiteralClass:
3618 case Expr::ObjCSubscriptRefExprClass:
3619 case Expr::ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExprClass:
3620 case Expr::ObjCAvailabilityCheckExprClass:
3621 case Expr::OffsetOfExprClass:
3622 case Expr::PredefinedExprClass:
3623 case Expr::ShuffleVectorExprClass:
3624 case Expr::ConvertVectorExprClass:
3625 case Expr::StmtExprClass:
3626 case Expr::TypeTraitExprClass:
3627 case Expr::ArrayTypeTraitExprClass:
3628 case Expr::ExpressionTraitExprClass:
3629 case Expr::VAArgExprClass:
3630 case Expr::CUDAKernelCallExprClass:
3631 case Expr::AsTypeExprClass:
3632 case Expr::PseudoObjectExprClass:
3633 case Expr::AtomicExprClass:
3634 case Expr::SourceLocExprClass:
3635 case Expr::FixedPointLiteralClass:
3636 {
3637 if (!NullOut) {
3638 // As bad as this diagnostic is, it's better than crashing.
3639 DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
3640 unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
3641 "cannot yet mangle expression type %0");
3642 Diags.Report(E->getExprLoc(), DiagID)
3643 << E->getStmtClassName() << E->getSourceRange();
3644 }
3645 break;
3646 }
3647
3648 case Expr::CXXUuidofExprClass: {
3649 const CXXUuidofExpr *UE = cast<CXXUuidofExpr>(E);
3650 if (UE->isTypeOperand()) {
3651 QualType UuidT = UE->getTypeOperand(Context.getASTContext());
3652 Out << "u8__uuidoft";
3653 mangleType(UuidT);
3654 } else {
3655 Expr *UuidExp = UE->getExprOperand();
3656 Out << "u8__uuidofz";
3657 mangleExpression(UuidExp, Arity);
3658 }
3659 break;
3660 }
3661
3662 // Even gcc-4.5 doesn't mangle this.
3663 case Expr::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass: {
3664 DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
3665 unsigned DiagID =
3666 Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
3667 "?: operator with omitted middle operand cannot be mangled");
3668 Diags.Report(E->getExprLoc(), DiagID)
3669 << E->getStmtClassName() << E->getSourceRange();
3670 break;
3671 }
3672
3673 // These are used for internal purposes and cannot be meaningfully mangled.
3674 case Expr::OpaqueValueExprClass:
3675 llvm_unreachable("cannot mangle opaque value; mangling wrong thing?");
3676
3677 case Expr::InitListExprClass: {
3678 Out << "il";
3679 mangleInitListElements(cast<InitListExpr>(E));
3680 Out << "E";
3681 break;
3682 }
3683
3684 case Expr::DesignatedInitExprClass: {
3685 auto *DIE = cast<DesignatedInitExpr>(E);
3686 for (const auto &Designator : DIE->designators()) {
3687 if (Designator.isFieldDesignator()) {
3688 Out << "di";
3689 mangleSourceName(Designator.getFieldName());
3690 } else if (Designator.isArrayDesignator()) {
3691 Out << "dx";
3692 mangleExpression(DIE->getArrayIndex(Designator));
3693 } else {
3694 assert(Designator.isArrayRangeDesignator() &&
3695 "unknown designator kind");
3696 Out << "dX";
3697 mangleExpression(DIE->getArrayRangeStart(Designator));
3698 mangleExpression(DIE->getArrayRangeEnd(Designator));
3699 }
3700 }
3701 mangleExpression(DIE->getInit());
3702 break;
3703 }
3704
3705 case Expr::CXXDefaultArgExprClass:
3706 mangleExpression(cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E)->getExpr(), Arity);
3707 break;
3708
3709 case Expr::CXXDefaultInitExprClass:
3710 mangleExpression(cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(E)->getExpr(), Arity);
3711 break;
3712
3713 case Expr::CXXStdInitializerListExprClass:
3714 mangleExpression(cast<CXXStdInitializerListExpr>(E)->getSubExpr(), Arity);
3715 break;
3716
3717 case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass:
3718 mangleExpression(cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)->getReplacement(),
3719 Arity);
3720 break;
3721
3722 case Expr::UserDefinedLiteralClass:
3723 // We follow g++'s approach of mangling a UDL as a call to the literal
3724 // operator.
3725 case Expr::CXXMemberCallExprClass: // fallthrough
3726 case Expr::CallExprClass: {
3727 const CallExpr *CE = cast<CallExpr>(E);
3728
3729 // <expression> ::= cp <simple-id> <expression>* E
3730 // We use this mangling only when the call would use ADL except
3731 // for being parenthesized. Per discussion with David
3732 // Vandervoorde, 2011.04.25.
3733 if (isParenthesizedADLCallee(CE)) {
3734 Out << "cp";
3735 // The callee here is a parenthesized UnresolvedLookupExpr with
3736 // no qualifier and should always get mangled as a <simple-id>
3737 // anyway.
3738
3739 // <expression> ::= cl <expression>* E
3740 } else {
3741 Out << "cl";
3742 }
3743
3744 unsigned CallArity = CE->getNumArgs();
3745 for (const Expr *Arg : CE->arguments())
3746 if (isa<PackExpansionExpr>(Arg))
3747 CallArity = UnknownArity;
3748
3749 mangleExpression(CE->getCallee(), CallArity);
3750 for (const Expr *Arg : CE->arguments())
3751 mangleExpression(Arg);
3752 Out << 'E';
3753 break;
3754 }
3755
3756 case Expr::CXXNewExprClass: {
3757 const CXXNewExpr *New = cast<CXXNewExpr>(E);
3758 if (New->isGlobalNew()) Out << "gs";
3759 Out << (New->isArray() ? "na" : "nw");
3760 for (CXXNewExpr::const_arg_iterator I = New->placement_arg_begin(),
3761 E = New->placement_arg_end(); I != E; ++I)
3762 mangleExpression(*I);
3763 Out << '_';
3764 mangleType(New->getAllocatedType());
3765 if (New->hasInitializer()) {
3766 if (New->getInitializationStyle() == CXXNewExpr::ListInit)
3767 Out << "il";
3768 else
3769 Out << "pi";
3770 const Expr *Init = New->getInitializer();
3771 if (const CXXConstructExpr *CCE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(Init)) {
3772 // Directly inline the initializers.
3773 for (CXXConstructExpr::const_arg_iterator I = CCE->arg_begin(),
3774 E = CCE->arg_end();
3775 I != E; ++I)
3776 mangleExpression(*I);
3777 } else if (const ParenListExpr *PLE = dyn_cast<ParenListExpr>(Init)) {
3778 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PLE->getNumExprs(); i != e; ++i)
3779 mangleExpression(PLE->getExpr(i));
3780 } else if (New->getInitializationStyle() == CXXNewExpr::ListInit &&
3781 isa<InitListExpr>(Init)) {
3782 // Only take InitListExprs apart for list-initialization.
3783 mangleInitListElements(cast<InitListExpr>(Init));
3784 } else
3785 mangleExpression(Init);
3786 }
3787 Out << 'E';
3788 break;
3789 }
3790
3791 case Expr::CXXPseudoDestructorExprClass: {
3792 const auto *PDE = cast<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(E);
3793 if (const Expr *Base = PDE->getBase())
3794 mangleMemberExprBase(Base, PDE->isArrow());
3795 NestedNameSpecifier *Qualifier = PDE->getQualifier();
3796 if (TypeSourceInfo *ScopeInfo = PDE->getScopeTypeInfo()) {
3797 if (Qualifier) {
3798 mangleUnresolvedPrefix(Qualifier,
3799 /*Recursive=*/true);
3800 mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(ScopeInfo->getType());
3801 Out << 'E';
3802 } else {
3803 Out << "sr";
3804 if (!mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(ScopeInfo->getType()))
3805 Out << 'E';
3806 }
3807 } else if (Qualifier) {
3808 mangleUnresolvedPrefix(Qualifier);
3809 }
3810 // <base-unresolved-name> ::= dn <destructor-name>
3811 Out << "dn";
3812 QualType DestroyedType = PDE->getDestroyedType();
3813 mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(DestroyedType);
3814 break;
3815 }
3816
3817 case Expr::MemberExprClass: {
3818 const MemberExpr *ME = cast<MemberExpr>(E);
3819 mangleMemberExpr(ME->getBase(), ME->isArrow(),
3820 ME->getQualifier(), nullptr,
3821 ME->getMemberDecl()->getDeclName(),
3822 ME->getTemplateArgs(), ME->getNumTemplateArgs(),
3823 Arity);
3824 break;
3825 }
3826
3827 case Expr::UnresolvedMemberExprClass: {
3828 const UnresolvedMemberExpr *ME = cast<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(E);
3829 mangleMemberExpr(ME->isImplicitAccess() ? nullptr : ME->getBase(),
3830 ME->isArrow(), ME->getQualifier(), nullptr,
3831 ME->getMemberName(),
3832 ME->getTemplateArgs(), ME->getNumTemplateArgs(),
3833 Arity);
3834 break;
3835 }
3836
3837 case Expr::CXXDependentScopeMemberExprClass: {
3838 const CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr *ME
3839 = cast<CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr>(E);
3840 mangleMemberExpr(ME->isImplicitAccess() ? nullptr : ME->getBase(),
3841 ME->isArrow(), ME->getQualifier(),
3842 ME->getFirstQualifierFoundInScope(),
3843 ME->getMember(),
3844 ME->getTemplateArgs(), ME->getNumTemplateArgs(),
3845 Arity);
3846 break;
3847 }
3848
3849 case Expr::UnresolvedLookupExprClass: {
3850 const UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E);
3851 mangleUnresolvedName(ULE->getQualifier(), ULE->getName(),
3852 ULE->getTemplateArgs(), ULE->getNumTemplateArgs(),
3853 Arity);
3854 break;
3855 }
3856
3857 case Expr::CXXUnresolvedConstructExprClass: {
3858 const CXXUnresolvedConstructExpr *CE = cast<CXXUnresolvedConstructExpr>(E);
3859 unsigned N = CE->arg_size();
3860
3861 if (CE->isListInitialization()) {
3862 assert(N == 1 && "unexpected form for list initialization");
3863 auto *IL = cast<InitListExpr>(CE->getArg(0));
3864 Out << "tl";
3865 mangleType(CE->getType());
3866 mangleInitListElements(IL);
3867 Out << "E";
3868 return;
3869 }
3870
3871 Out << "cv";
3872 mangleType(CE->getType());
3873 if (N != 1) Out << '_';
3874 for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I) mangleExpression(CE->getArg(I));
3875 if (N != 1) Out << 'E';
3876 break;
3877 }
3878
3879 case Expr::CXXConstructExprClass: {
3880 const auto *CE = cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E);
3881 if (!CE->isListInitialization() || CE->isStdInitListInitialization()) {
3882 assert(
3883 CE->getNumArgs() >= 1 &&
3884 (CE->getNumArgs() == 1 || isa<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(CE->getArg(1))) &&
3885 "implicit CXXConstructExpr must have one argument");
3886 return mangleExpression(cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E)->getArg(0));
3887 }
3888 Out << "il";
3889 for (auto *E : CE->arguments())
3890 mangleExpression(E);
3891 Out << "E";
3892 break;
3893 }
3894
3895 case Expr::CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass: {
3896 const auto *CE = cast<CXXTemporaryObjectExpr>(E);
3897 unsigned N = CE->getNumArgs();
3898 bool List = CE->isListInitialization();
3899
3900 if (List)
3901 Out << "tl";
3902 else
3903 Out << "cv";
3904 mangleType(CE->getType());
3905 if (!List && N != 1)
3906 Out << '_';
3907 if (CE->isStdInitListInitialization()) {
3908 // We implicitly created a std::initializer_list<T> for the first argument
3909 // of a constructor of type U in an expression of the form U{a, b, c}.
3910 // Strip all the semantic gunk off the initializer list.
3911 auto *SILE =
3912 cast<CXXStdInitializerListExpr>(CE->getArg(0)->IgnoreImplicit());
3913 auto *ILE = cast<InitListExpr>(SILE->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImplicit());
3914 mangleInitListElements(ILE);
3915 } else {
3916 for (auto *E : CE->arguments())
3917 mangleExpression(E);
3918 }
3919 if (List || N != 1)
3920 Out << 'E';
3921 break;
3922 }
3923
3924 case Expr::CXXScalarValueInitExprClass:
3925 Out << "cv";
3926 mangleType(E->getType());
3927 Out << "_E";
3928 break;
3929
3930 case Expr::CXXNoexceptExprClass:
3931 Out << "nx";
3932 mangleExpression(cast<CXXNoexceptExpr>(E)->getOperand());
3933 break;
3934
3935 case Expr::UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExprClass: {
3936 const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *SAE = cast<UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr>(E);
3937
3938 if (!SAE->isInstantiationDependent()) {
3939 // Itanium C++ ABI:
3940 // If the operand of a sizeof or alignof operator is not
3941 // instantiation-dependent it is encoded as an integer literal
3942 // reflecting the result of the operator.
3943 //
3944 // If the result of the operator is implicitly converted to a known
3945 // integer type, that type is used for the literal; otherwise, the type
3946 // of std::size_t or std::ptrdiff_t is used.
3947 QualType T = (ImplicitlyConvertedToType.isNull() ||
3948 !ImplicitlyConvertedToType->isIntegerType())? SAE->getType()
3949 : ImplicitlyConvertedToType;
3950 llvm::APSInt V = SAE->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Context.getASTContext());
3951 mangleIntegerLiteral(T, V);
3952 break;
3953 }
3954
3955 switch(SAE->getKind()) {
3956 case UETT_SizeOf:
3957 Out << 's';
3958 break;
3959 case UETT_PreferredAlignOf:
3960 case UETT_AlignOf:
3961 Out << 'a';
3962 break;
3963 case UETT_VecStep: {
3964 DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
3965 unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
3966 "cannot yet mangle vec_step expression");
3967 Diags.Report(DiagID);
3968 return;
3969 }
3970 case UETT_OpenMPRequiredSimdAlign: {
3971 DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
3972 unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
3973 DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
3974 "cannot yet mangle __builtin_omp_required_simd_align expression");
3975 Diags.Report(DiagID);
3976 return;
3977 }
3978 }
3979 if (SAE->isArgumentType()) {
3980 Out << 't';
3981 mangleType(SAE->getArgumentType());
3982 } else {
3983 Out << 'z';
3984 mangleExpression(SAE->getArgumentExpr());
3985 }
3986 break;
3987 }
3988
3989 case Expr::CXXThrowExprClass: {
3990 const CXXThrowExpr *TE = cast<CXXThrowExpr>(E);
3991 // <expression> ::= tw <expression> # throw expression
3992 // ::= tr # rethrow
3993 if (TE->getSubExpr()) {
3994 Out << "tw";
3995 mangleExpression(TE->getSubExpr());
3996 } else {
3997 Out << "tr";
3998 }
3999 break;
4000 }
4001
4002 case Expr::CXXTypeidExprClass: {
4003 const CXXTypeidExpr *TIE = cast<CXXTypeidExpr>(E);
4004 // <expression> ::= ti <type> # typeid (type)
4005 // ::= te <expression> # typeid (expression)
4006 if (TIE->isTypeOperand()) {
4007 Out << "ti";
4008 mangleType(TIE->getTypeOperand(Context.getASTContext()));
4009 } else {
4010 Out << "te";
4011 mangleExpression(TIE->getExprOperand());
4012 }
4013 break;
4014 }
4015
4016 case Expr::CXXDeleteExprClass: {
4017 const CXXDeleteExpr *DE = cast<CXXDeleteExpr>(E);
4018 // <expression> ::= [gs] dl <expression> # [::] delete expr
4019 // ::= [gs] da <expression> # [::] delete [] expr
4020 if (DE->isGlobalDelete()) Out << "gs";
4021 Out << (DE->isArrayForm() ? "da" : "dl");
4022 mangleExpression(DE->getArgument());
4023 break;
4024 }
4025
4026 case Expr::UnaryOperatorClass: {
4027 const UnaryOperator *UO = cast<UnaryOperator>(E);

4029 /*Arity=*/1);

4038 // binary operator.

4041 mangleExpression(AE->getRHS());
4042 break;
4043 }

4046 case Expr::BinaryOperatorClass: {

4063 mangleExpression(CO->getRHS(), Arity);

4110 break;

4191 Out << 'E';

4233 Out << 'L';

4235 mangleType(E->getType());
4236 Out << 'E';
4237 break;

4242 // fallthrough
4243
4244 case Expr::CXXNullPtrLiteralExprClass: {

4247 }

4328
4329/// Mangle an expression which refers to a parameter variable.
4330///
4331/// <expression> ::= <function-param>
4332/// <function-param> ::= fp <top-level CV-qualifiers> _ # L == 0, I == 0
4333/// <function-param> ::= fp <top-level CV-qualifiers>
4334/// <parameter-2 non-negative number> _ # L == 0, I > 0
4335/// <function-param> ::= fL <L-1 non-negative number>
4336/// p <top-level CV-qualifiers> _ # L > 0, I == 0
4337/// <function-param> ::= fL <L-1 non-negative number>
4338/// p <top-level CV-qualifiers>
4339/// <I-1 non-negative number> _ # L > 0, I > 0
4340///
4341/// L is the nesting depth of the parameter, defined as 1 if the
4342/// parameter comes from the innermost function prototype scope
4343/// enclosing the current context, 2 if from the next enclosing
4344/// function prototype scope, and so on, with one special case: if
4345/// we've processed the full parameter clause for the innermost
4346/// function type, then L is one less. This definition conveniently
4347/// makes it irrelevant whether a function's result type was written
4348/// trailing or leading, but is otherwise overly complicated; the
4349/// numbering was first designed without considering references to
4350/// parameter in locations other than return types, and then the
4351/// mangling had to be generalized without changing the existing
4352/// manglings.
4353///
4354/// I is the zero-based index of the parameter within its parameter
4355/// declaration clause. Note that the original ABI document describes
4356/// this using 1-based ordinals.
4357void CXXNameMangler::mangleFunctionParam(const ParmVarDecl *parm) {
4358 unsigned parmDepth = parm->getFunctionScopeDepth();
4359 unsigned parmIndex = parm->getFunctionScopeIndex();
4360
4361 // Compute 'L'.
4362 // parmDepth does not include the declaring function prototype.
4363 // FunctionTypeDepth does account for that.
4364 assert(parmDepth < FunctionTypeDepth.getDepth());
4365 unsigned nestingDepth = FunctionTypeDepth.getDepth() - parmDepth;
4366 if (FunctionTypeDepth.isInResultType())
4367 nestingDepth--;
4368
4369 if (nestingDepth == 0) {
4370 Out << "fp";
4371 } else {
4372 Out << "fL" << (nestingDepth - 1) << 'p';
4373 }
4374
4375 // Top-level qualifiers. We don't have to worry about arrays here,
4376 // because parameters declared as arrays should already have been
4377 // transformed to have pointer type. FIXME: apparently these don't
4378 // get mangled if used as an rvalue of a known non-class type?
4379 assert(!parm->getType()->isArrayType()
4380 && "parameter's type is still an array type?");
4381
4382 if (const DependentAddressSpaceType *DAST =
4383 dyn_cast<DependentAddressSpaceType>(parm->getType())) {
4384 mangleQualifiers(DAST->getPointeeType().getQualifiers(), DAST);
4385 } else {
4386 mangleQualifiers(parm->getType().getQualifiers());
4387 }
4388
4389 // Parameter index.
4390 if (parmIndex != 0) {
4391 Out << (parmIndex - 1);
4392 }
4393 Out << '_';
4394}
4395
4396void CXXNameMangler::mangleCXXCtorType(CXXCtorType T,
4397 const CXXRecordDecl *InheritedFrom) {
4398 // <ctor-dtor-name> ::= C1 # complete object constructor
4399 // ::= C2 # base object constructor
4400 // ::= CI1 <type> # complete inheriting constructor
4401 // ::= CI2 <type> # base inheriting constructor
4402 //
4403 // In addition, C5 is a comdat name with C1 and C2 in it.
4404 Out << 'C';
4405 if (InheritedFrom)
4406 Out << 'I';
4407 switch (T) {
4408 case Ctor_Complete:
4409 Out << '1';
4410 break;
4411 case Ctor_Base:
4412 Out << '2';
4413 break;
4414 case Ctor_Comdat:
4415 Out << '5';
4416 break;
4417 case Ctor_DefaultClosure:
4418 case Ctor_CopyingClosure:
4419 llvm_unreachable("closure constructors don't exist for the Itanium ABI!");
4420 }
4421 if (InheritedFrom)
4422 mangleName(InheritedFrom);
4423}
4424
4425void CXXNameMangler::mangleCXXDtorType(CXXDtorType T) {
4426 // <ctor-dtor-name> ::= D0 # deleting destructor
4427 // ::= D1 # complete object destructor
4428 // ::= D2 # base object destructor
4429 //
4430 // In addition, D5 is a comdat name with D1, D2 and, if virtual, D0 in it.
4431 switch (T) {
4432 case Dtor_Deleting:
4433 Out << "D0";
4434 break;
4435 case Dtor_Complete:
4436 Out << "D1";
4437 break;
4438 case Dtor_Base:
4439 Out << "D2";
4440 break;
4441 case Dtor_Comdat:
4442 Out << "D5";
4443 break;
4444 }
4445}

4472
4473void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateArg(TemplateArgument A) {
4474 // <template-arg> ::= <type> # type or template
4475 // ::= X <expression> E # expression
4476 // ::= <expr-primary> # simple expressions
4477 // ::= J <template-arg>* E # argument pack
4478 if (!A.isInstantiationDependent() || A.isDependent())
4479 A = Context.getASTContext().getCanonicalTemplateArgument(A);
4480
4481 switch (A.getKind()) {
4482 case TemplateArgument::Null:
4483 llvm_unreachable("Cannot mangle NULL template argument");
4484
4485 case TemplateArgument::Type:
4486 mangleType(A.getAsType());
4487 break;
4488 case TemplateArgument::Template:
4489 // This is mangled as <type>.
4490 mangleType(A.getAsTemplate());
4491 break;
4492 case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
4493 // <type> ::= Dp <type> # pack expansion (C++0x)
4494 Out << "Dp";
4495 mangleType(A.getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern());
4496 break;
4497 case TemplateArgument::Expression: {
4498 // It's possible to end up with a DeclRefExpr here in certain
4499 // dependent cases, in which case we should mangle as a
4500 // declaration.
4501 const Expr *E = A.getAsExpr()->IgnoreParens();
4502 if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
4503 const ValueDecl *D = DRE->getDecl();
4504 if (isa<VarDecl>(D) || isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4505 Out << 'L';
4506 mangle(D);
4507 Out << 'E';
4508 break;
4509 }
4510 }
4511
4512 Out << 'X';
4513 mangleExpression(E);
4514 Out << 'E';
4515 break;
4516 }
4517 case TemplateArgument::Integral:
4518 mangleIntegerLiteral(A.getIntegralType(), A.getAsIntegral());
4519 break;
4520 case TemplateArgument::Declaration: {
4521 // <expr-primary> ::= L <mangled-name> E # external name
4522 // Clang produces AST's where pointer-to-member-function expressions
4523 // and pointer-to-function expressions are represented as a declaration not
4524 // an expression. We compensate for it here to produce the correct mangling.
4525 ValueDecl *D = A.getAsDecl();
4526 bool compensateMangling = !A.getParamTypeForDecl()->isReferenceType();
4527 if (compensateMangling) {
4528 Out << 'X';
4529 mangleOperatorName(OO_Amp, 1);
4530 }
4531
4532 Out << 'L';
4533 // References to external entities use the mangled name; if the name would
4534 // not normally be mangled then mangle it as unqualified.
4535 mangle(D);
4536 Out << 'E';
4537
4538 if (compensateMangling)
4539 Out << 'E';
4540
4541 break;
4542 }
4543 case TemplateArgument::NullPtr: {
4544 // <expr-primary> ::= L <type> 0 E
4545 Out << 'L';
4546 mangleType(A.getNullPtrType());
4547 Out << "0E";
4548 break;
4549 }
4550 case TemplateArgument::Pack: {
4551 // <template-arg> ::= J <template-arg>* E
4552 Out << 'J';
4553 for (const auto &P : A.pack_elements())
4554 mangleTemplateArg(P);
4555 Out << 'E';
4556 }
4557 }
4558}
4559
4560void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateParameter(unsigned Index) {
4561 // <template-param> ::= T_ # first template parameter
4562 // ::= T <parameter-2 non-negative number> _
4563 if (Index == 0)
4564 Out << "T_";
4565 else
4566 Out << 'T' << (Index - 1) << '_';
4567}
4568
4569void CXXNameMangler::mangleSeqID(unsigned SeqID) {
4570 if (SeqID == 1)
4571 Out << '0';
4572 else if (SeqID > 1) {
4573 SeqID--;
4574
4575 // <seq-id> is encoded in base-36, using digits and upper case letters.
4576 char Buffer[7]; // log(2**32) / log(36) ~= 7
4577 MutableArrayRef<char> BufferRef(Buffer);
4578 MutableArrayRef<char>::reverse_iterator I = BufferRef.rbegin();
4579
4580 for (; SeqID != 0; SeqID /= 36) {
4581 unsigned C = SeqID % 36;
4582 *I++ = (C < 10 ? '0' + C : 'A' + C - 10);
4583 }
4584
4585 Out.write(I.base(), I - BufferRef.rbegin());
4586 }
4587 Out << '_';
4588}

4590void CXXNameMangler::mangleExistingSubstitution(TemplateName tname) {
4591 bool result = mangleSubstitution(tname);
4592 assert(result && "no existing substitution for template name");
4593 (void) result;
4594}

4596// <substitution> ::= S <seq-id> _
4597// ::= S_
4598bool CXXNameMangler::mangleSubstitution(const NamedDecl *ND) {
4599 // Try one of the standard substitutions first.
4600 if (mangleStandardSubstitution(ND))
4601 return true;
4602
4603 ND = cast<NamedDecl>(ND->getCanonicalDecl());
4604 return mangleSubstitution(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(ND));
4605}

4607/// Determine whether the given type has any qualifiers that are relevant for
4608/// substitutions.
4609static bool hasMangledSubstitutionQualifiers(QualType T) {
4610 Qualifiers Qs = T.getQualifiers();
4611 return Qs.getCVRQualifiers() || Qs.hasAddressSpace() || Qs.hasUnaligned();

4614bool CXXNameMangler::mangleSubstitution(QualType T) {
4615 if (!hasMangledSubstitutionQualifiers(T)) {
4616 if (const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>())
4617 return mangleSubstitution(RT->getDecl());
4618 }
4619
4620 uintptr_t TypePtr = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(T.getAsOpaquePtr());
4621
4622 return mangleSubstitution(TypePtr);
4623}

4634bool CXXNameMangler::mangleSubstitution(uintptr_t Ptr) {
4635 llvm::DenseMap<uintptr_t, unsigned>::iterator I = Substitutions.find(Ptr);
4636 if (I == Substitutions.end())
4637 return false;
4638
4639 unsigned SeqID = I->second;
4640 Out << 'S';
4641 mangleSeqID(SeqID);
4642
4643 return true;
4644}

4646static bool isCharType(QualType T) {
4647 if (T.isNull())
4648 return false;
4649
4650 return T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Char_S) ||
4651 T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Char_U);
4652}
4653
4654/// Returns whether a given type is a template specialization of a given name
4655/// with a single argument of type char.
4656static bool isCharSpecialization(QualType T, const char *Name) {
4657 if (T.isNull())
4658 return false;
4659
4660 const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>();
4661 if (!RT)
4662 return false;
4663
4664 const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *SD =
4665 dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RT->getDecl());
4666 if (!SD)
4667 return false;
4668
4669 if (!isStdNamespace(getEffectiveDeclContext(SD)))
4670 return false;
4671
4672 const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs = SD->getTemplateArgs();
4673 if (TemplateArgs.size() != 1)
4674 return false;
4675
4676 if (!isCharType(TemplateArgs[0].getAsType()))
4677 return false;
4678
4679 return SD->getIdentifier()->getName() == Name;
4680}
4681
4682template <std::size_t StrLen>
4683static bool isStreamCharSpecialization(const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl*SD,
4684 const char (&Str)[StrLen]) {
4685 if (!SD->getIdentifier()->isStr(Str))
4686 return false;
4687
4688 const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs = SD->getTemplateArgs();
4689 if (TemplateArgs.size() != 2)
4690 return false;
4691
4692 if (!isCharType(TemplateArgs[0].getAsType()))
4693 return false;
4694
4695 if (!isCharSpecialization(TemplateArgs[1].getAsType(), "char_traits"))
4696 return false;
4697
4698 return true;
4699}
4700
4701bool CXXNameMangler::mangleStandardSubstitution(const NamedDecl *ND) {
4702 // <substitution> ::= St # ::std::
4703 if (const NamespaceDecl *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(ND)) {
4704 if (isStd(NS)) {
4705 Out << "St";
4706 return true;
4707 }
4708 }
4709
4710 if (const ClassTemplateDecl *TD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(ND)) {
4711 if (!isStdNamespace(getEffectiveDeclContext(TD)))
4712 return false;
4713
4714 // <substitution> ::= Sa # ::std::allocator
4715 if (TD->getIdentifier()->isStr("allocator")) {
4716 Out << "Sa";
4717 return true;
4718 }
4719
4720 // <<substitution> ::= Sb # ::std::basic_string
4721 if (TD->getIdentifier()->isStr("basic_string")) {
4722 Out << "Sb";
4723 return true;
4724 }
4725 }
4726
4727 if (const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *SD =
4728 dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(ND)) {
4729 if (!isStdNamespace(getEffectiveDeclContext(SD)))
4730 return false;
4731
4732 // <substitution> ::= Ss # ::std::basic_string<char,
4733 // ::std::char_traits<char>,
4734 // ::std::allocator<char> >
4735 if (SD->getIdentifier()->isStr("basic_string")) {
4736 const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs = SD->getTemplateArgs();
4737
4738 if (TemplateArgs.size() != 3)
4739 return false;
4740
4741 if (!isCharType(TemplateArgs[0].getAsType()))
4742 return false;
4743
4744 if (!isCharSpecialization(TemplateArgs[1].getAsType(), "char_traits"))
4745 return false;
4746
4747 if (!isCharSpecialization(TemplateArgs[2].getAsType(), "allocator"))
4748 return false;
4749
4750 Out << "Ss";
4751 return true;
4752 }
4753
4754 // <substitution> ::= Si # ::std::basic_istream<char,
4755 // ::std::char_traits<char> >
4756 if (isStreamCharSpecialization(SD, "basic_istream")) {
4757 Out << "Si";
4758 return true;
4759 }
4760
4761 // <substitution> ::= So # ::std::basic_ostream<char,
4762 // ::std::char_traits<char> >
4763 if (isStreamCharSpecialization(SD, "basic_ostream")) {
4764 Out << "So";
4765 return true;
4766 }
4767
4768 // <substitution> ::= Sd # ::std::basic_iostream<char,
4769 // ::std::char_traits<char> >
4770 if (isStreamCharSpecialization(SD, "basic_iostream")) {
4771 Out << "Sd";
4772 return true;
4773 }
4774 }
4775 return false;
4776}

4778void CXXNameMangler::addSubstitution(QualType T) {
4779 if (!hasMangledSubstitutionQualifiers(T)) {
4780 if (const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
4781 addSubstitution(RT->getDecl());
4782 return;
4783 }
4784 }
4785
4786 uintptr_t TypePtr = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(T.getAsOpaquePtr());
4787 addSubstitution(TypePtr);
4788}

4790void CXXNameMangler::addSubstitution(TemplateName Template) {
4791 if (TemplateDecl *TD = Template.getAsTemplateDecl())
4792 return addSubstitution(TD);
4793
4794 Template = Context.getASTContext().getCanonicalTemplateName(Template);
4795 addSubstitution(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Template.getAsVoidPointer()));
4796}
4797
4798void CXXNameMangler::addSubstitution(uintptr_t Ptr) {
4799 assert(!Substitutions.count(Ptr) && "Substitution already exists!");
4800 Substitutions[Ptr] = SeqID++;
4801}
4802
4803void CXXNameMangler::extendSubstitutions(CXXNameMangler* Other) {
4804 assert(Other->SeqID >= SeqID && "Must be superset of substitutions!");
4805 if (Other->SeqID > SeqID) {
4806 Substitutions.swap(Other->Substitutions);
4807 SeqID = Other->SeqID;
4808 }
4809}

4811CXXNameMangler::AbiTagList
4812CXXNameMangler::makeFunctionReturnTypeTags(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
4813 // When derived abi tags are disabled there is no need to make any list.
4814 if (DisableDerivedAbiTags)
4815 return AbiTagList();
4816
4817 llvm::raw_null_ostream NullOutStream;
4818 CXXNameMangler TrackReturnTypeTags(*this, NullOutStream);
4819 TrackReturnTypeTags.disableDerivedAbiTags();
4820
4821 const FunctionProtoType *Proto =
4822 cast<FunctionProtoType>(FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionType>());
4823 FunctionTypeDepthState saved = TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.push();
4824 TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
4825 TrackReturnTypeTags.mangleType(Proto->getReturnType());
4826 TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.leaveResultType();
4827 TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
4828
4829 return TrackReturnTypeTags.AbiTagsRoot.getSortedUniqueUsedAbiTags();
4830}
4831
4832CXXNameMangler::AbiTagList
4833CXXNameMangler::makeVariableTypeTags(const VarDecl *VD) {
4834 // When derived abi tags are disabled there is no need to make any list.
4835 if (DisableDerivedAbiTags)
4836 return AbiTagList();
4837
4838 llvm::raw_null_ostream NullOutStream;
4839 CXXNameMangler TrackVariableType(*this, NullOutStream);
4840 TrackVariableType.disableDerivedAbiTags();
4841
4842 TrackVariableType.mangleType(VD->getType());
4843
4844 return TrackVariableType.AbiTagsRoot.getSortedUniqueUsedAbiTags();
4845}

4857/// Mangles the name of the declaration D and emits that name to the given
4858/// output stream.
4859///
4860/// If the declaration D requires a mangled name, this routine will emit that
4861/// mangled name to \p os and return true. Otherwise, \p os will be unchanged
4862/// and this routine will return false. In this case, the caller should just
4863/// emit the identifier of the declaration (\c D->getIdentifier()) as its
4864/// name.
4865void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXName(const NamedDecl *D,
4866 raw_ostream &Out) {
4867 assert((isa<FunctionDecl>(D) || isa<VarDecl>(D)) &&
4868 "Invalid mangleName() call, argument is not a variable or function!");
4869 assert(!isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(D) && !isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(D) &&
4870 "Invalid mangleName() call on 'structor decl!");
4871
4872 PrettyStackTraceDecl CrashInfo(D, SourceLocation(),
4873 getASTContext().getSourceManager(),
4874 "Mangling declaration");
4875
4876 CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, D);
4877 Mangler.mangle(D);
4878}

4905
4906void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleThunk(const CXXMethodDecl *MD,
4907 const ThunkInfo &Thunk,
4908 raw_ostream &Out) {
4909 // <special-name> ::= T <call-offset> <base encoding>
4910 // # base is the nominal target function of thunk
4911 // <special-name> ::= Tc <call-offset> <call-offset> <base encoding>
4912 // # base is the nominal target function of thunk
4913 // # first call-offset is 'this' adjustment
4914 // # second call-offset is result adjustment
4915
4916 assert(!isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) &&
4917 "Use mangleCXXDtor for destructor decls!");
4918 CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
4919 Mangler.getStream() << "_ZT";
4920 if (!Thunk.Return.isEmpty())
4921 Mangler.getStream() << 'c';
4922
4923 // Mangle the 'this' pointer adjustment.
4924 Mangler.mangleCallOffset(Thunk.This.NonVirtual,
4925 Thunk.This.Virtual.Itanium.VCallOffsetOffset);
4926
4927 // Mangle the return pointer adjustment if there is one.
4928 if (!Thunk.Return.isEmpty())
4929 Mangler.mangleCallOffset(Thunk.Return.NonVirtual,
4930 Thunk.Return.Virtual.Itanium.VBaseOffsetOffset);
4931
4932 Mangler.mangleFunctionEncoding(MD);
4933}

4935void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXDtorThunk(
4936 const CXXDestructorDecl *DD, CXXDtorType Type,
4937 const ThisAdjustment &ThisAdjustment, raw_ostream &Out) {
4938 // <special-name> ::= T <call-offset> <base encoding>
4939 // # base is the nominal target function of thunk
4940 CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, DD, Type);
4941 Mangler.getStream() << "_ZT";
4942
4943 // Mangle the 'this' pointer adjustment.
4944 Mangler.mangleCallOffset(ThisAdjustment.NonVirtual,
4945 ThisAdjustment.Virtual.Itanium.VCallOffsetOffset);
4946
4947 Mangler.mangleFunctionEncoding(DD);
4948}
